              "category": "Lead Actor",
              "note": "Daniel Day-Lewis as Reynolds Woodcock, her favorite PTA film and, she argues, its most quotable, weaponizable character."
            },
            {
              "title": "Punch-Drunk Love",
              "year": 2002,
              "category": "Lead Actress",
              "note": "Emily Watson as Lena Leonard, warm and intrigued by Barry's pudding-miles scheme instead of reading him as a weirdo."
            },
            {
              "title": "Magnolia",
              "year": 1999,
              "category": "Supporting Actor",
              "note": "Tom Cruise as Frank T.J. Mackey; she takes him in supporting because to her all of Magnolia is supporting."
            },
            {
              "title": "Phantom Thread",
              "year": 2017,
              "category": "Supporting Actress",
              "note": "Lesley Manville as Cyril Woodcock, who says little, controls everything, and never looks up from the teacup."
            },
            {
              "title": "Boogie Nights",
              "year": 1997,
              "category": "One Scene Star",
